{"TopicId":180966,"ForumId":46,"TopicTitle":"How do you link to another thread?","CreatedByName":"Duck McFuddle","CreatedById":188882,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-12-29T17:44:59Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Duck McFuddle","CreatedById":188882,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-12-29T17:44:59Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nJust what the title says. I see people all the time showing a little box thingy with the other thread in it, but I don\u0027t know how to do that. I just put a link like\u00A0\u003Ca href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/forum/32-ksp-discussion/\u0026amp;do=add\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003Ethis\u003C/a\u003E. (That was a link to this post by the way)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo how do I do what other people do?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"razark","CreatedById":32993,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-12-29T17:52:15Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nJust put the URL of the post you want in the post.\u00A0 The forum will automatically convert it for you.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFor example, simply pasting \u0022\u003Cspan\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/180966-how-do-you-link-to-another-thread/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003Ehttps://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/180966-how-do-you-link-to-another-thread/\u0022\u003C/a\u003E into the input box will convert it to: \u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed1743979381\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/180966-how-do-you-link-to-another-thread/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022 style=\u0022height:224px;max-width:500px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt also lets you insert a youtube video this way:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022true\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 height=\u0022270\u0022 src=\u0022https://www.youtube.com/embed/8-ca8AYblFg?feature=oembed\u0022 width=\u0022480\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222018-12-29T17:55:20Z\u0022 title=\u002212/29/2018 05:55  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00225 yr\u0022\u003EDecember 29, 2018\u003C/time\u003E by razark\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Snark","CreatedById":125662,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-12-29T18:09:26Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMoving to Kerbal Network, since this is a question about the forum rather than about KSP itself.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Duck McFuddle","CreatedById":188882,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-12-29T21:25:06Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAh. Okay.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}